Baingan Bharta
==============

Ingredients
-----------

- 2 pounds eggplant
- 2 tablespoons lime juice
- 2 to 3 tablespoons vegetable oil
- 1 medium onion, peeled and chopped
- 3 cloves garlic, peeled and finely chopped or 3/4 teaspoon granulated garlic
- 1 tablespoon finely chopped ginger root, or 1/2 teaspoon powdered ginger
- 2 hot green chiles, finely sliced
- 1 pound fresh tomatoes, chopped, or one can crushed tomatoes
- 1/2 teaspoon turmeric
- 1 teaspoon kosher salt or to taste
- 1/2 teaspoon ground coriander
- 2 teaspoons garam masala
- 1/2 cup chopped cilantro, thin stems included

Directions
----------

Pierce eggplant several times with sharp knife. Roast over open flame until skin is charred and eggplant starts to collapse. Let cool a bit, then peel the skins off and discard stem. Mash in a bowl with lime juice.

Saute the chopped onion in a large pan until lightly browned, add salt, chiles, garlic, coriander, turmeric and ginger. Cook briefly stirring constantly. Add tomatoes and cook until soft (if fresh).

Add eggplant, simmer covered for 10-15 minutes. Add garam masala and simmer for another couple of minutes. Remove from heat and stir in cilantro.